com.radiantlogic.iddm.base

Class ResponseEntity<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.radiantlogic.iddm.base.ResponseEntity<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The backend-specific data object class carried by instances
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasStatus, Response
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LdapResponse

    public abstract class ResponseEntity<T>
extends Object
implements Response, HasStatus
    Abstract base class for storing arbitrary data returned from third-party backends with protocol-specific status codes.

    This class uses generics to allow callers to store arbitrary data types while still providing IDDM and the SDK a standard way to access that data and move it through the system. It is abstract because there is no concept of a generic "status code" that applies to all possible response types.

    Callers should implement this class and provide their own protocol-specific StatusCode implementation. The connector framework in IDDM will rely on StatusCode#isError() to perform generic mapping from custom StatusCode implementations to LDAP-specific status codes.
